Soldiers patrol the streets in an attempt to enforce a nationwide lockdown, aimed at limiting the spread of coronavirus disease (COVID-19), in Alexandra township, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Defence Force has exonerated the soldiers implicated in the death of Collins Khosa in Alexandra, Johannesburg. They were accused of beating the 40-year-old man to death in April. Khosa died hours after the alleged incident. An SANDF investigation found Collins did not die as a result of the altercation. WATCH: Collins Khosa's widow wants justice The police investigation is still ongoing. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.